<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
            <h1 class="mb-4">Enchant Courier Admin Guide</h1>
            
            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">System Overview</h2>
                    <p>Enchant Courier is a Node.js-based courier management system developed by Abdullah Shakur. This guide provides technical documentation for administrators and developers.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Technical Stack</h2>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled">
                        <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Node.js, Express.js</li>
                        <li><strong>Database:</strong> MongoDB with Mongoose ODM</li>
                        <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Passport.js with Local Strategy</li>
                        <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> EJS Templates, Bootstrap 5</li>
                        <li><strong>Styling:</strong> SASS/SCSS</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Project Structure</h2>
                    <pre class="bg-light p-3 rounded">
├── config/           # Configuration files
├── controllers/      # Route controllers
├── models/          # Database models
├── public/          # Static assets
│   ├── css/        # Compiled CSS
│   ├── js/         # Client-side JavaScript
│   └── images/     # Image assets
├── routes/          # Route definitions
├── utils/           # Utility functions
└── views/           # EJS templates
    ├── layouts/    # Layout templates
    ├── partials/   # Reusable components
    └── [feature]/  # Feature-specific views
                    </pre>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Authentication Flow</h2>
                    <ol>
                        <li>User submits login credentials</li>
                        <li>Passport.js validates credentials against MongoDB</li>
                        <li>Session is created and stored in MongoDB</li>
                        <li>User is redirected to appropriate dashboard</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Order Management</h2>
                    <p>The system handles three types of orders:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>All Orders:</strong> Complete order listing</li>
                        <li><strong>Delivered Orders:</strong> Successfully delivered shipments</li>
                        <li><strong>Returned Orders:</strong> Returned or failed deliveries</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Development Guidelines</h2>
                    <h3 class="h5 mt-3">Code Style</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Use ES6+ JavaScript features</li>
                        <li>Follow MVC architecture pattern</li>
                        <li>Implement proper error handling</li>
                        <li>Write meaningful comments</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 class="h5 mt-3">Security Best Practices</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Always validate user input</li>
                        <li>Use environment variables for sensitive data</li>
                        <li>Implement proper session management</li>
                        <li>Follow the principle of least privilege</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card mb-4">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Troubleshooting</h2>
                    <h3 class="h5 mt-3">Common Issues</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Authentication Failures:</strong> Check MongoDB connection and user credentials</li>
                        <li><strong>Form Submission Errors:</strong> Verify client-side validation and server-side processing</li>
                        <li><strong>Database Issues:</strong> Monitor MongoDB connection and query performance</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

